Cross-Region Disaster Recovery for Mission-Critical SQL Server

Redundant database architecture for a mission-critical SQL Server environment. 
The solution provides local High Availability (HA) through Multi-AZ deployment and a secondary layer of Disaster Recovery (DR) via cross-region asynchronous replication using AWS DMS.

Multi-Region Disaster Recovery (DR) and High Availability (HA).
Assumptions: SQL Server Standard Edition (License Included), db.m5.large (2 vCPU, 8GB RAM), 200GB GP3 Storage.

Monthly Budget: 1321 USD on AWS 

Architecture Strategy

Primary Layer (Local HA): AWS RDS for SQL Server in Multi-AZ configuration. This handles synchronous replication across two Availability Zones in the primary region to protect
against data center failure.
Secondary Layer (Regional DR): AWS DMS configured for Continuous Data Capture (CDC).
This performs asynchronous replication to a target RDS instance in a completely different AWS Region (e.g., US-East-1 to US-West-2) to protect against a full regional outage.

