Cost Optimization strategy

The "SQL Server Tax" (Licensing)
In AWS, "License Included" pricing for SQL Server is roughly 4–5x more expensive than open-source engines like PostgreSQL.
Multi-AZ effectively doubles your instance cost because AWS maintains a standby instance for you.
AWS DMS Instance: For a production SQL Server environment, a T3 instance might suffer from "CPU Credit" exhaustion during heavy replication. I recommend an R5 or R6i instance for stable memory 
handling of the transaction logs. Cost: ~$0.25/hour for an r5.large.
Networking:Inbound to AWS: Free.
Cross-Region Transfer: AWS charges ~$0.02 per GB for data moving from one region to another.

Technical Implementation 

Source Configuration: Enabled MS-CDC (Change Data Capture) on the primary Multi-AZ instance.
DMS Instance: Provisioned a Replication Instance in the source region.
Endpoint Security: Configured VPC Peering or AWS Transit Gateway to allow secure, low-latency traffic between the two regions.
Task Optimization: * Set up a Full Load + Ongoing Replication task.
Tuned the MinTransactionSize to balance latency vs. throughput.
Handled SQL Server-specific metadata (Users, Logins, and Jobs) which DMS doesn't replicate automatically.

